data.title: Cboe Global Markets appoints JJ Kinahan as Senior VP for Retail Expansion & Alternative Investment Products.
data.description: Chicago, October 30, 2025 - Cboe Global Markets, Inc. (Cboe: CBOE), a prominent derivatives and securities exchange platform, revealed that JJ Kinahan is set to become the Senior Vice President, overseeing Retail Expansion and Alternative Investment Products. Mr. Kinahan's appointment signifies a key move for Cboe as they aim to strengthen their retail operations with a focus on alternative investment offerings.

data.title: BCP to sell Gray Casualty & Surety Company, a top surety bond provider, in Baton Rouge, for undisclosed amount.
data.description: In Baton Rouge, Louisiana on October 30, 2025, BCP, a private equity management firm specializing in services and infrastructure, revealed their plan to sell The Gray Casualty & Surety Company, also known as Gray Surety. Gray Surety is a prominent provider of surety bonds catering to midsize and up-and-coming contractors. The transaction marks a significant move in the industry.

This development allows for enhanced monitoring and oversight.

data.title: Cohen & Steers, Inc. (NYSE: CNS) declares $0.62 per share dividend for Q4 2025, payable on Nov 20 to stockholders of record.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, Cohen & Steers, Inc announced a cash dividend of $0.62 per share for the fourth quarter of 2025. This dividend is payable on November 20, 2025, to stockholders of record as of the close of business. The company's Board of Directors made this decision, and the stocks are listed on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol CNS.

data.title: COPT Defense buys 142,000 sq ft building in Chantilly, VA for $40.2M, fully occupied by top US Defense Contractor.
data.description: In Columbia, Maryland, COPT Defense Properties (NYSE: CDP) recently disclosed its purchase of Stonegate I, a Class A office building spanning 142,000 square feet located at 15050 Conference Center Drive in Chantilly, VA. This acquisition amounted to a total of $40.2 million. The office building is currently fully leased by a leading U.S. Defense Contractor, holding a spot in the top 20, with a decade left on their lease agreement. This property marks the ninth location within the Company's portfolio. Stonegate I's construction was completed in 2XXX.

Such developments suggest promising financial growth for the company in the foreseeable future.

data.title: DXC Technology Q2 FY2026: Revenue $3.16B (-2.5% YoY), Bookings $2.7B, EBIT margin 4.4%, EPS $0.20 (-13% YoY).
data.description: The company's total revenue for the year amounted to $3.16 billion, showing a decrease of 2.5% year-over-year, or a 4.2% decline on an organic basis. Bookings reported were approximately $2.7 billion, with a trailing twelve-month book-to-bill ratio of 1.08x. The EBIT margin was calculated at 4.4%, while the adjusted EBIT margin stood at 8.0%. Diluted earnings per share were $0.20, depicting a decrease of 13.0% year-over-year. Non-GAAP diluted earnings were not provided in the data.

data.title: Valmont to attend Baird’s Global Industrial Conference in Chicago. NYSE: VMI to host investor meetings on Nov 12.

data.title: Rockwell Automation increases dividend to $1.38 per share on common stock, payable Dec. 10, 2025, up from $1.31 last quarter.
data.description: The Board of Directors at Rockwell Automation, Inc. (NYSE: ROK) has announced a quarterly dividend of $1.38 per share on its common stock. This dividend will be paid on Dec. 10, 2025, to shareholders of record as of Nov. 17, 2025. The increase from the previous quarter's dividend of $1.31 showcases the company's robust financial standing and dedication to providing returns to its shareholders. Rockwell Automation remains focused on delivering value to its investors.

data.title: Agilent will report Q4 FY2025 results on Nov. 24 after market close, with a conference call at 1:30 p.m. PST.
data.description: Agilent Technologies Inc. will be sharing its financial performance for Q4 of fiscal year 2025 following the stock market closure on November 24. The firm, listed as NYSE: A, has arranged a conference call at 1:30 p.m. PST on the same day to deliberate on these results. Interested parties can access the listen-only conference call webcast through a provided link in the Events section of Agilent’s Investor Relations website. Additionally, a recording of the call will be archived on the website for a period of 90 days.

data.title: Cloudflare reports Q3 2025 financial results: revenue growth accelerates to 31% YoY, demonstrating increasing momentum. CEO optimistic about company's innovation and execution.
data.description: In San Francisco, Cloudflare, Inc. (NYSE: NET), a prominent connectivity cloud company, released its financial performance for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. CEO Matthew Prince highlighted the company's strong momentum, noting a 31% year-over-year revenue growth in the third quarter. This marks the second consecutive quarter of accelerated revenue growth. Prince emphasized Cloudflare's commitment to innovation and execution, indicating a positive outlook for the company's future success.
